er(s) by any means other than displaying a Link to the Advertiser on Your Website. Your promotional activities must have been approved in advance by INTERSERVER, who may deem Your promotional activities inappropriate and a material breach of this Agreement in INTERSERVER's sole discretion. Our network quality department reviews publisher conduct and suspected fraudulent, abusive, or otherwise illegal content or activity by You that is forbidden by the laws and regulations of the United States or this Agreement through Your promotional methods, or that is perpetrated through use of the Network Service, is grounds for recording, website blocking, deleting and/or reporting to the relevant authorities of the aforesaid conduct and behavior as well as immediate termination of this Agreement or deactivation of Your Account (at the sole discretion of INTERSERVER)</div>
