                            <p>Pursuant to the current laws and regulations in the United States, You acknowledge that any payment made by INTERSERVER to you under this Agreement shall be paid in RMB. In the event that You expect to receive payment in any of the other currencies that INTERSERVER supports (as may be amended by INTERSERVER), You shall satisfy all the following conditions: (i) You shall embrace the advertising business qualifications both in the UNITED STATES and in all other applicable countries and regions; (ii) If You expect to be paid in a currency of a specific country or region other than the UNITED STATES, You shall maintain the same business relationship with INTERSERVER in that country or region; (iii) You have gained approval from the Chinese Administrative Authority of Foreign Exchange to open a Current Account for Foreign Exchange; and (iv) The payment made by INTERSERVER in other currency shall be an acceptable item for your Current Account for Foreign Exchange in accordance with the Chinese laws and regulations. Notwithstanding the foregoing, You acknowledge that INTERSERVER is entitled, in its sole discretion to choose RMB as the currency of settlement if INTERSERVER considers You have failed to satisfy any aforementioned conditions, or the payment You request to pay in other currency reaches or exceeds $50,000 or equivalent thereof. The conversion rate shall be determined in accordance with INTERSERVER's operating standards using the rates prevailing upon the date that payment is made to You, or upon the basis of historical conversion rates if rates are unavailable. The number or amount of Transactions, credits for Payouts, and debits for Charge-backs, as calculated by INTERSERVER, shall be final and binding on You.</p>
